page.title: 10FORESTRY CONTINUED
page.content: Delamere/Eddisbury {FORESTRY CONTINUED} Most of the woodland warblers are present,also cuckoos,turtle doves, redstarts & treepipits are frequent visitors.Breeding birds include redpoll,woodcock,& sometimes siskins & pied flycatchers. Crossbills can be seen in winter prising open pine cones for seeds. Mammals also live in the forest.Foxes are abundant,& badgers find the light sandy soil ideal for making setts. Americn grey squirrels have taken the place of the indiginous red squirrel & pose a problem for the foresters because of the damage they cause by bark stripping.
